 style=";text-align:right;direction:rtl"><div class="controls-wrapper" style=";text-align:right;direction:rtl"></div><ol class="slides" style=";text-align:right;direction:rtl"><li class="wrapper item-1" role="list-item" style=";text-align:right;direction:rtl"><figure class="figure"><img decoding="async" width="536" height="383" src="https://www.sciencenews.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/061723_amazon_slide-1-536x383.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium" alt="A photo of water with skinny trees growing throughout the waterway." loading="lazy" data-attachment-id="3125389" data-permalink="https://www.sciencenews.org/061723_amazon_slide-1" data-orig-file="https://www.sciencenews.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/061723_amazon_slide-1.jpg" data-orig-size="680,486" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;Ramesh M. Thadani&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="061723_amazon_slide-1" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p>;The Amazon basin is home to a variety of ecosystems. Várzeas (shown) are located in lowland floodplain areas that seasonally become inundated with nutrient-rich waters.&lt;/p>;
